<span id="freeTextContainer750349602152083229">A.k.a. A gathering light.<br/>On July 12, 1906, the body of a young woman named Grace Brown was pulled from the waters of Big Moose Lake in the Adirondack Mountains. This is the fact on which the writer based her story of Mattie. A young girl from an agricultural background who met Grace Brown in the hotel where she worked. It&apos;s a well written, sweet story, despite the hardships.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText750349602152083229" style="display:none">A.k.a. A gathering light.<br />On July 12, 1906, the body of a young woman named Grace Brown was pulled from the waters of Big Moose Lake in the Adirondack Mountains. This is the fact on which the writer based her story of Mattie. A young girl from an agricultural background who met Grace Brown in the hotel where she worked. It's a well written, sweet story, despite the hardships.<br /></span>
